        "level": "h1"
      },
      "text": "React useState Hook",
      "level": "h1"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The React useState Hook allows us to track state in a function component.",
      "html": "<p class=\"intro\">The React <code>useState</code> Hook allows us to track state in a function component.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "State generally refers to data or properties that need to be tracking in an application.",
      "html": "<p class=\"intro\">State generally refers to data or properties that need to be tracking in an application.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "Import useState",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "To use the useState Hook, we first need to import it into our component.",
      "html": "<p>To use the <code>useState</code> Hook, we first need to <code>import</code> it into our component.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "python",
        "tryItLink": null,
        "syntaxHighlighting": [],
        "classList": [
          "w3-white",
          "language-jsx"
        ],
        "isNotranslate": false
      },
      "code": "import\n\n{\nuseState\n}\n\nfrom\n\n\"react\"\n;",
      "language": "python",
      "code_html": "<pre class=\"w3-white language-jsx\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword keyword-import\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword keyword-from\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>",
      "code_classes": [
        "w3-white",
        "language-jsx"
      ],
      "tryItLink": null,
      "syntax_highlighting_data": [],
      "class_list": [
        "w3-white",
        "language-jsx"
      ],
      "is_notranslate": false
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Notice that we are destructuring useState from react as it is a named export.",
      "html": "<p>Notice that we are destructuring <code>useState</code> from <code>react</code> as it is a named export.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "ES6 section",
          "href": "https://www.w3schools.com/react_es6.asp",
          "title": ""
        }
      ],
      "text": "To learn more about destructuring, check out the ES6 section .",
      "html": "<p>To learn more about destructuring, check out the <a href=\"react_es6.asp\">ES6 section</a>.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "Initialize useState",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "We initialize our state by calling useState in our function component.",
      "html": "<p>We initialize our state by calling <code>useState</code> in our function component.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "useState accepts an initial state and returns two values:",
      "html": "<p><code>useState</code> accepts an initial state and returns two values:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "javascript",
        "tryItLink": null,
        "syntaxHighlighting": [],
        "classList": [
          "w3-white",
          "language-jsx"
        ],
        "isNotranslate": false
      },
      "code": "import\n\n{\nuseState\n}\n\nfrom\n\n\"react\"\n;\n\n\n\nfunction\n\nFavoriteColor\n(\n)\n\n{\n\n\nconst\n\n[\ncolor\n,\nsetColor\n]\n\n=\n\nuseState\n(\n\"\"\n)\n;\n\n\n}",
      "language": "javascript",
      "code_html": "<pre class=\"w3-white language-jsx\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword keyword-import\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword keyword-from\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword keyword-function\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">FavoriteColor</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword keyword-const\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>color<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> setColor<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>",
      "code_classes": [
        "w3-white",
        "language-jsx"
      ],
      "tryItLink": null,
      "syntax_highlighting_data": [],
      "class_list": [
        "w3-white",
        "language-jsx"
      ],
      "is_notranslate": false
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Notice that again, we are destructuring the returned values from useState .",
      "html": "<p>Notice that again, we are destructuring the returned values from <code>useState</code>.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The first value, color , is our current state.",
      "html": "<p>The first value, <code>color</code>, is our current state.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "The second value, setColor , is the function that is used to update our state.",
      "html": "<p>The second value, <code>setColor</code>, is the function that is used to update our state.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "These names are variables that can be named anything you would like.",
      "html": "<p>These names are variables that can be named anything you would like.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Lastly, we set the initial state to an empty string: useState(\"\")",
      "html": "<p>Lastly, we set the initial state to an empty string: <code>useState(\"\")</code></p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "Read State",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "We can now include our state anywhere in our component.",
      "html": "<p>We can now include our state anywhere in our component.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "javascript",
        "tryItLink": null,
        "syntaxHighlighting": [],
        "classList": [
          "w3-white",
          "language-jsx"
        ],
        "isNotranslate": false
      },
      "code": "import\n\n{\nuseState\n}\n\nfrom\n\n\"react\"\n;\n\n\nimport\nReactDOM\nfrom\n\n\"react-dom/client\"\n;\n\n\n\nfunction\n\nFavoriteColor\n(\n)\n\n{\n\n\nconst\n\n[\ncolor\n,\nsetColor\n]\n\n=\n\nuseState\n(\n\"red\"\n)\n;\n\n\n\nreturn\n\n<\nh1\n>\nMy favorite color is\n{\ncolor\n}\n!\n</\nh1\n>\n\n\n}\n\n\n\nconst\nroot\n=\nReactDOM\n.\ncreateRoot\n(\ndocument\n.\ngetElementById\n(\n'root'\n)\n)\n;\n\nroot\n.\nrender\n(\n<\nFavoriteColor\n\n/>\n)\n;",
      "language": "html",
      "code_html": "<pre class=\"w3-white language-jsx\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword keyword-import\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useState <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword keyword-from\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword keyword-import\">import</span> ReactDOM <span class=\"token keyword keyword-from\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react-dom/client\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword keyword-function\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">FavoriteColor</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword keyword-const\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>color<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> setColor<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"red\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword keyword-return\">return</span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">My favorite color is </span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>color<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token plain-text\">!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword keyword-const\">const</span> root <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> ReactDOM<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">createRoot</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'root'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nroot<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">FavoriteColor</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>",
